Egypt’s national team coach Carlos Queiroz cancelled yesterday’s training session with the Democratic Republic of Congo’s (DRC) national team and postponed the Pharaoh’s flight to Cameroon until tomorrow. Egypt’s national team was scheduled to train with the DRC’s team on Thursday in preparation for the 2021 African Cup of Nations (AFCON) that will kick off on January 9, in Cameroon. The national team was also supposed to travel to Cameroon today, however Queiroz postponed the flight.   Covid knocks out Aubameyang     Eagles holds first session in Garoua     Ighalo out of AFCON 2021   The Portuguese coach also decided to continue closed training sessions as a precautionary measure for fear of any coronavirus infections. The Pharaohs underwent PCR tests yesterday’s morning in preparation for the flight to Cameroon, which has been moved to Saturday morning to give the players enough time to rest before traveling. - Advertisement - The seven-time African champions will be playing in Group D with Nigeria, Sudan, and Guinea Bissau, and will begin their campaign for the AFCON with a clash against the Nigerian Super Eagles on 11 January.